#: docs/zh/triton_api/Compiler_Hint_Ops/assume.md:20
msgid "### 2.3 дҪҝз”Ёж–№жі•"
msgstr "### 2.3 Usage"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Compiler_Hint_Ops/assume.md:22
msgid "`assume` ж“ҚдҪңе…Ғи®ёејҖеҸ‘иҖ…еңЁзЎ®дҝқжӯЈзЎ®жҖ§зҡ„еүҚжҸҗдёӢпјҢеё®еҠ©зј–иҜ‘еҷЁз”ҹжҲҗжӣҙй«ҳж•Ҳзҡ„д»Јз ҒгҖӮ"
msgstr "The `assume` operation allows developers to help the compiler generate more efficient code while ensuring correctness."

#. type: code
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Compiler_Hint_Ops/assume.md:24
msgid ""
"```python\n"
"import triton.language as tl\n"
"\n"
"@triton.jit\n"
"def basic_assume_example(x_ptr, y_ptr, BLOCK_SIZE: tl.constexpr):\n"
"    # еҒҮи®ҫBLOCK_SIZEжҳҜ2зҡ„е№Ӯж¬ЎпјҢзј–иҜ‘еҷЁеҸҜд»ҘеҹәдәҺжӯӨдјҳеҢ–йҷӨжі•иҝҗз®—\n"
"    tl.assume((BLOCK_SIZE & (BLOCK_SIZE - 1)) == 0)\n"
"\n"
"    offsets = tl.arange(0, BLOCK_SIZE)\n"
"    x = tl.load(x_ptr + offsets)\n"
"    y = tl.load(y_ptr + offsets)\n"
"\n"
"    # зј–иҜ‘еҷЁзҹҘйҒ“BLOCK_SIZEжҳҜ2зҡ„е№Ӯж¬ЎпјҢеҸҜд»ҘдјҳеҢ–йҷӨжі•дёәз§»дҪҚж“ҚдҪң\n"
"    result = x // BLOCK_SIZE + y % BLOCK_SIZE\n"
"    tl.store(y_ptr + offsets, result)\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

